      "type": "lesson",
      "itemId": "lesson-cct-001",
      "difficulty": 1,
      "themes": [
        "basics",
        "calculation"
      ],
      "position": {
        "fen": "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"
      },
      "title": "CCT: checks, captures, threats",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "kind": "markdown",
          "markdown": "# Blunder check\nBefore every move, run **CCT**:\n- **Checks**\n- **Captures**\n- **Threats**\n\nThis habit prevents most one-move blunders."
        },
        {
          "kind": "markdown",
          "markdown": "In the next diagram, you can win immediately by delivering checkmate in one move."
        },
        {
          "kind": "diagram",
          "fen": "7k/5KQ1/8/8/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 1",
          "caption": "Mate pattern: queen supported by king"
        },
        {
          "kind": "tryMove",
          "fen": "7k/5KQ1/8/8/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 1",
          "prompt": "Play the checkmating move.",
          "expectedUci": "g7g8",
          "wrongBehavior": "hint",
          "hintMarkdown": "Move the queen from **g7** to **g8**."
        },
        {
          "kind": "markdown",
          "markdown": "Nice. Supported mates (queen/rook protected by the king) are a great early pattern to memorize."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "lesson",
      "itemId": "lesson-opening-principles-001",
      "difficulty": 1,
      "themes": [
        "opening",
        "basics"
