      "position": {
        "fen": "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"
      },
      "title": "Opening principles (development & king safety)",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "kind": "markdown",
          "markdown": "# Opening principles\nGood openings are usually about **development** and **king safety**, not memorizing.\n\nKey ideas:\n- Fight for the center (e4/d4)\n- Develop knights/bishops\n- Castle early\n- Don't move the same piece repeatedly without a reason"
        },
        {
          "kind": "diagram",
          "fen": "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1",
          "caption": "Starting position"
        },
        {
          "kind": "tryMove",
          "fen": "rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1",
          "prompt": "Play 1.e4.",
          "expectedUci": "e2e4",
          "wrongBehavior": "hint",
          "hintMarkdown": "Click the pawn on **e2**, then **e4**."
        },
        {
          "kind": "markdown",
          "markdown": "Great. 1.e4 or 1.d4 are both good ways to fight for the center."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
