    {
      "type": "lesson",
      "itemId": "lesson-stalemate-001",
      "difficulty": 2,
      "themes": [
        "endgame",
        "draw"
      ],
      "position": {
        "fen": "7k/5K2/6Q1/8/8/8/8/8 b - - 0 1"
      },
      "title": "Stalemate basics",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "kind": "markdown",
          "markdown": "# Stalemate\nIf the side to move has **no legal moves** and is **not in check**, the game is a draw.\n\nThis often happens when the defender has only a king."
        },
        {
          "kind": "diagram",
          "fen": "7k/5K2/6Q1/8/8/8/8/8 b - - 0 1",
          "caption": "Black to move: is this a draw?"
        },
        {
          "kind": "markdown",
          "markdown": "Try making any move for Black. If there are no legal moves, it is a stalemate draw."
        }
      ]
    },
